{
  "_comment": "Copy to config/sources.json to add your own sources without editing code. Each entry merges into the built-in registry and becomes available as --no-<name> / --<name>-hint CLI flags. For ready-made sources (GitHub, Jira, Postgres, ...), copy a bundle from examples/sources/<name>/ instead of hand-writing one. Required fields include `transport` (http-oauth | stdio | cli | native) and `read_only_mechanism` (how read-only is enforced: url-suffix:<s> | server-flag:<s> | tool-allowlist:<s> | arg-absent:<s> | scope:<s> | statement-allowlist | credential-only | native). The agent still needs a way to reach the source (e.g. an MCP server in .mcp.json), except for `cli`/`native` sources like the gsc bundle that reach their system without one; these specs only describe it for planning and prompting.",
  "sources": {
    "zendesk": {
      "key": "zendesk_mcp",
      "hint_field": "focus",
      "label": "Zendesk focus",
      "display_label": "Zendesk",
      "freshness_caveat_group": "docs",
      "transport": "stdio",
      "read_only_mechanism": "credential-only",
      "plan_line": "Zendesk for support tickets and customer-reported signals.",
      "base_notes": "Search support tickets, conversations, and macros for customer-reported signals. Read-only — never reply to or modify tickets."
    }
  }
}
